exif:ImageDescription: Pat Garrett, second from the right, sitting in front of a Jaffa, Prager & Co. store in Roswell, New Mexico, in 1887. Sheriff of Lincoln County during the Lincoln County War, Garrett was responsible for the deaths of Tom O'Folliard, Charles Bowdre, and, in July 1881, Billy the Kid. Photo: Courtesy of Center for Southwest Research, UNM Libraries.
